The paper discusses compressed sensing, low rank matrix recovery, and phaseless estimation, which are all subfields of signal processing. The focus is on structured random measurement matrices, which are used to acquire signals in a more efficient and stable manner. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions matrix completion and phase estimation from magnitudes of Fourier type measurements, which are topics that fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, respectively.
